<title type="html"><![CDATA[different kind of hardware request - Nintendo in car]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6546&amp;p=63503#p63503"><![CDATA[
For the OS, use an Ubuntu variant. For a bargain-basement SSD, use a suitably fast CF card through a <a href="http://www.addonics.com/products/flash_memory_reader/ad44midecf.asp" class="postlink">CF-to-parallel-ATA adapter</a>.<br /><br />"Abandonware" is a myth. To be 100% legal, you have to build a CopyNES and dump your own Game Paks. It'd be easier if the Retrode supported NES, but it doesn't.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Jun 30, 2010 6:45 am</p><hr />
