<title type="html"><![CDATA[different kind of hardware request - Nintendo in car]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6546&amp;p=63495#p63495"><![CDATA[
The NES connector is metric, it's 2.5mm.  The pins will get shorted in a .1" (2.54mm) connector.  A game genie sounds like the way to go.  Another source of connectors would be a cheap clone that takes NES carts.<br /><br />The Famicom connector, however is .1" pitch (2.54mm).<br /><br />As for wireless, there was a company called Messiah a while back, that had released some wireless controllers.  The receiver shouldn't need power (the NES controller port supplies +5V).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Tue Jun 29, 2010 8:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
